div.div: @drag0n141 Nope you don't. I've been using the same config for about 4 months now. gluetun is used as the network for these containers, since gluetun is connected to the proxy (traefik) network; containers on the gluetun network i.e. the one using gleutun as their network stack also have access to the proxy network.
I Think the files are wrong, you need to do the traefik labels on the gluetun docker.
